# Version Release Checklist

When bumping the version in `package.json`, **always** complete every step below before committing:

1. **Update `package.json` version** — e.g. `"version": "1.0.5"`.
2. **Update README.md** — replace **all** occurrences of the old version:
   - Badge: `![Version X.Y.Z](https://img.shields.io/badge/version-X.Y.Z-green.svg)`
   - VSIX filenames: `cursor-remote-X.Y.Z.vsix` (appears in install instructions).
3. **Build**: `npm run build`
4. **Package**: `npm run package` — produces `cursor-remote-X.Y.Z.vsix`.
5. **Delete the old `.vsix`** from the repo root (only one prebuilt vsix should be tracked).
6. **Commit** with message format: `vX.Y.Z: <short description of changes>`
7. **Tag the release**: `git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "vX.Y.Z: <short description>"`
8. **Push** with tags and large buffer: `git -c http.postBuffer=157286400 push origin main --tags`
9. **Create a GitHub Release** with the `.vsix` attached (the self-updater downloads it):

```bash
TOKEN=$(git remote get-url origin | sed 's|https://\(.*\)@github.com.*|\1|')

# Create the release
RELEASE_ID=$(curl -s -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: token $TOKEN" \
  -H "Accept: application/vnd.github.v3+json" \
  https://api.github.com/repos/puntorigen/cursor-remote/releases \
  -d '{"tag_name":"vX.Y.Z","name":"vX.Y.Z","body":"Release notes","draft":false}' \
  | python3 -c "import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['id'])")

# Upload the .vsix asset
curl -s -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: token $TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/octet-stream" \
  "https://uploads.github.com/repos/puntorigen/cursor-remote/releases/$RELEASE_ID/assets?name=cursor-remote-X.Y.Z.vsix" \
  --data-binary @cursor-remote-X.Y.Z.vsix
```
